    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-12-09T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-12-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="140"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d140">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 Pacific War/888: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Uruguay</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dawson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Montevideo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-12-09">December 9,
                            1941</date>.<lb/>[Received December 9—10:42 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>529. This afternoon the Uruguayan Chamber of Deputies voted unanimously that a
                    message of solidarity be sent the United States House of Representatives. The
                    Chamber also voted unanimously a resolution supporting and approving the
                    Uruguayan Government’s decree of yesterday transmitted in my telegram 523.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dawson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
